text.__SUMMARY__:
Baeckea muricata is a shrub endemic to Western Australia.The spreading shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1 metre (1.0 to 3.3 ft) and a diameter of 1.5 metres (4.9 ft). It blooms between October and December producing white flowers.
It is found on sand plains in central areas of the Wheatbelt  region of Western Australia where it grows in sandy and gravelly clay soils.
